        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-11T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="274"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1696: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-11T12:00:00+07:00"
                            >February 11, 1944—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 11—7:40
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>277. I learn from General Hearn, Chief of Staff,<note n="53a" xml:id="d274fn53a"
                        >To General Stilwell.</note> that General Yu Ta-wei, Chief of Ordnance,
                    Chinese Army, has been discussing with him possible use of United States
                    lend-lease equipment by Chinese Government forces against Chinese Communists.
                    Hearn says he informed Yu that it would be impossible for Chinese successfully
                    to explain to American people such use of American equipment and later after
                    communicating with Stilwell he informed Yu that Stilwell does not wish any of
                    the American equipped forces used in Northwest. In reply to my question, Hearn
                    said War Department had not been informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
